---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Receptionist — Build Crystal"
  description="A Crystal receptionist answers every call in under a ring, books and reschedules, and never calls in sick. ~$2,100/mo, ~50% of a human hire, ready in 3-5 days. First 28 days free."
  active="workers"
>
  <article class="worker">
    <div class="frame">
      <header class="worker-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">Available for hire</p>
        <h1>Receptionist.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          A virtual employee for your front desk. Answers every call in under a ring, books and reschedules against
          your existing calendar, logs every interaction, and escalates judgment calls to you.
        </p>
        <div class="head-meta">
          <div><strong>~$2,100 / mo</strong><span>~50% of the human hire</span></div>
          <div><strong>24 / 7</strong><span>coverage, no sick days</span></div>
          <div><strong>3&ndash;5 days</strong><span>from call to live</span></div>
          <div><strong>28 days</strong><span>free pilot</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="head-ctas">
          <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary" data-hire data-role="receptionist">Hire a receptionist</a>
          <a href="#details" class="btn btn-secondary">See what it does</a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="worker-section" id="details">
        <h2>What a Crystal receptionist does.</h2>
        <ul class="does">
          <li>Answers every call in under a ring &mdash; identifies, captures intent, routes or books.</li>
          <li>Books and reschedules appointments against your existing calendar.</li>
          <li>Logs every interaction and follows up the next morning.</li>
          <li>Escalates judgment calls to the owner with a one-line summary.</li>
          <li>Works nights, weekends, holidays. Doesn't take lunch.</li>
          <li>Every correction sticks &mdash; the same mistake doesn't happen twice.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="worker-section">
        <h2>What it doesn't do.</h2>
        <p>
          Anything that needs hands or a face. Walk-ins, signing for packages, in-person greetings &mdash; that's still
          a human job, and we're upfront about it. Some businesses split the role: front desk stays human for the
          physical part, while phones, calendar, and email move to a Crystal receptionist.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="worker-section">
        <h2>The math.</h2>
        <table class="math-table">
          <tbody>
            <tr><th>Market salary (loaded)</th><td>~$50,000 / yr</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Crystal receptionist</th><td>~$2,100 / mo</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Coverage</th><td>24 / 7</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Setup time</th><td>3&ndash;5 business days</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Free trial</th><td>28 days, no card</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Included</th><td>Worker, build-out, training, integrations, ongoing corrections, maintenance, updates.</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Not included</th><td>Your Anthropic API bill &mdash; you own the account, we don't resell it.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section class="worker-section">
        <h2>The honest part.</h2>
        <p>
          Day one is rough, like any new hire. We tell you that up front. By day 30 it's outworking your last three.
          Every correction makes it permanently smarter. Every night it reviews what it learned and shows up the next
          morning a little better than it was. That's the trade: a rough first week in exchange for a worker that
          compounds.
        </p>
        <p>
          You're still in charge. There's a kill switch. If it's not working on day 28, we remove ourselves from your
          tools the same day.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="worker-cta">
        <h3>Hiring a receptionist?</h3>
        <p>Book a 15-minute working session. We'll show you what one of ours would do in your shop.</p>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary" data-hire data-role="receptionist">Book a working session</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .worker { padding: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5rem) 0 clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4rem); }
  .worker-head { max-width: 56rem; margin-bottom: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); }
  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .worker-head h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 4.8vw, 3.5rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .worker-head .lede {
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.6vw, 1.2rem);
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    max-width: 52ch;
    margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .head-meta {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(10rem, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .head-meta strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .head-meta span {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
  }
  .head-ctas { display: flex; gap: 0.6rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  .worker-section {
    padding: 2rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    max-width: 56rem;
  }
  .worker-section h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.4vw, 1.8rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .worker-section p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    max-width: 62ch;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .worker-section p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .does {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
  .does li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.7rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .does li::before {
    content: "";
    width: 5px; height: 5px;
    background: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin-top: 0.65em;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .math-table {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 56rem;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .math-table th, .math-table td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .math-table th {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    width: 32%;
  }
  .math-table td { color: var(--ink); }

  .worker-cta {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding: 2rem 2.25rem;
    background: var(--accent-wash);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    max-width: 56rem;
  }
  .worker-cta h3 { margin: 0 0 0.4rem; font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .worker-cta p { margin: 0 0 1rem; color: var(--ink-2); }
</style>
